<error-message-context>

<title>Error Messages with Context and Solutions</title>

<rules>
- Always include what the user was trying to accomplish when an error occurs
- Provide the specific error details and what caused it
- Suggest at least one actionable fix or workaround
- Reference the exact location where the error occurred (file:line when applicable)
- Keep error messages concise but informative
- Avoid technical jargon unless necessary for the fix
</rules>

<examples>
<example type="good">
```
Error: Failed to connect to database while trying to fetch user profile.
Cause: Connection timeout after 30 seconds at db/connection.js:45
Fix: Check if the database server is running and accessible on port 5432
```
</example>
</examples>

